                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d43">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A4/17b: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harvey</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-07-13T18:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 13, 1921—6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>398. Have received from France, Italy and China direct responses that they will
                    be glad to receive invitation to conference. In case of Great Britain have only
                    your 573, July 10, 9 p.m. that Prime Minister “says statement is admirable; he
                    wholly approves.” This, of course, quite sufficient but would like direct
                    expression of approval of invitation similar to that received from other Powers
                    which would be available for publication if desired.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
